messages.message:
Hm, I think "Working" might not be so true. I've been checking on why Cypress has been so weird lately and at least one of the issues is that some apps / deployments related tests are timing out trying to look for a specific app, and it looks like it's due to apps not being able to be deleted, causing the app list to get bigger and bigger. I double checked by trying to delete one manually.
We might need some deeper investigation into why deletion is failing.
Also, I checked it using the sandbox spun up for my PR (https://crafting-cyp--pr-66109-cypress-instabase.instabase.site.sandboxes.run/), but I don't think it should matter

Let's move this off this thread so Kerry doesn't get pinged - I'm pretty sure this is a known issue with ground truth sets and we've stopped running this test because of this bug. It doesn't have to do with the services Kerry mentioned
